  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Given a query q and a corpus C, a dense retriever R retrieves the top-k relevant contexts C q = {c 1,..., c k }.",
    "In standard RAG pipelines, a large language model (LLM) generates the answer based on a prompt that includes the query and the retrieved documents:",
    "where Prompt gen is a prompting template that provides instructions and structures the input for the LLM.",
    "This paradigm allows the LLM to produce answers grounded in retrieved evidence, thereby reducing hallucinations (Huang et al., 2023).",
    "While advances in long-context LLMs (Liu et al., 2025) suggest potential to bypass retrieval altogether, practical limitations remain: effective context utilization is still far below advertised limits (Modarressi et al., 2025), and processing long sequences significantly increases inference cost and latency."
  ],
